{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c9f4a1e2-3b7d-4f08-a2c5-d8e6f0b1c234",
    "name": "ETH-Liq-LTV-Coll1-1minute-seconds",
    "description": "ACTUS DeFi ETH 1-minute loan: COMPETING BEHAVIORAL RISKS simulation — SECONDS granularity.\n\nTWO behavioral models run simultaneously:\n  1. TwoDimensionalPrepaymentModel — voluntary rate-driven deleveraging\n     (spread × age surface, checked every 10 seconds = 6 check points over 1 minute)\n  2. CollateralLTVModel — protocol-enforced LTV-driven liquidation\n     (second-level monitoring = 60 check times over 1 minute)\n\nScenario: Intraday ETH micro flash-crash tick pattern\n  ETH: $2,210 → $2,196 (~0.63% decline over 1 minute, with tick-level noise)\n     Derived from end-of-minute values of the 1-hour minutely simulation\n     Models historical ETH sub-minute tick volatility pattern\n  Rate: 6.850% → 6.858% (gradual second-level rise)\n     Derived from end-of-period values of the 1-minute window of the hourly simulation\n  Collateral: 3.0 ETH, initial LTV = 75.4%  ($5000 / (3 × $2,210))\n\nSECONDS design:\n  Index data: 61 second-level points each (T09:01:00 → T09:02:00)\n  LTV monitoring: 60 times (every second T09:01:01 → T09:02:00)\n  Prepayment checks: 6 (every 10 seconds: T09:01:10, ..., T09:02:00)\n  Rate resets: every second (cycle PT1SL1)\n\nKey LTV thresholds (Aave V3 calibrated):\n  ltvThreshold  = 75%  → partial repay to target 65%\n  liquidation   = 82.5% → full liquidation\n  LTV hits 75%   when ETH ≈ $2,222  (already breached at start: ETH=$2,210, LTV=75.4%)\n  LTV hits 82.5% when ETH ≈ $2,020\n  Starting LTV = 75.4% — ABOVE threshold, breach fires immediately at T09:01:01\n\nScholarly Basis:\n  - Deng, Quigley & Van Order (2000), Econometrica: Competing risks framework\n  - Schwartz & Torous (1989, 1993): Rate-driven prepayment modeling\n  - Qin et al. (2021): DeFi liquidation mechanisms & thresholds\n  - Heimbach & Huang (2024), BIS WP 1171: DeFi leverage & voluntary buffers\n  - Lehar & Parlour (2022), BIS WP 1062: Systemic fragility, cascades\n  - Sadeghi (2025): Liquidation dynamics & transaction fees\n  - Aspris & Svec (2025): Skilled vs unskilled DeFi risk management\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
